Package edu.mit.jwi.content.compare

Provides classes that encode the sorting order of the Wordnet data file lines, to enable binary searching.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
ICommentDetector Objects that implement this interface act as both detectors for comment lines in data resources, and comparators that say how comment lines are ordered, if at all.
 

Class Summary
CommentComparator Basic implementation of a comment detector that is designed for comments found at the head of Wordnet 2.1 & 3.0 dictionary files.
DataLineComparator A comparator that captures the ordering of lines in Wordnet 2.1 data files (data.adv or adv.dat files, for example).
ExceptionLineComparator A comparator that captures the ordering of lines in Wordnet 2.1 exception files (exc.adv or adv.exc files, for example).
IndexLineComparator A comparator that captures the ordering of lines in Wordnet 2.1 index files (index.adv or adv.idx files, for example).
StaticComparators Provides several static comparators that are used in the default Wordnet content types.
 

Package edu.mit.jwi.content.compare Description

Provides classes that encode the sorting order of the Wordnet data file lines, to enable binary searching.
